<section class="page-hero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Cheap Flights</p>
  <h1>Find better fares with flexible search habits</h1>
  <p>Use flexible dates, nearby airports, and sensible cabin filters before committing to a route.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-grid">
  <article>
    <h2>Flexible dates</h2>
    <p>Airfares can shift sharply by day of week, school holidays, and event demand. Compare adjacent departure and return dates before booking.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <h2>Route options</h2>
    <p>Search nearby airports and one-stop routes when direct flights are expensive. A small routing change can create a materially lower fare.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <h2>Cabin filters</h2>
    <p>Keep the cabin class intentional. Premium economy and business fare sales can be worth watching separately from economy fares.</p>
  </article>
</section>

